        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 3:10PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 310 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lawson, or 8 miles east of El Dorado, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Calion and Pigeon Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
